			<ns0:name>mseaborn@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/mseaborn@chromium.org/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">On Windows, Chromium's nacl_process_host.cc creates a new debugger thread for every NaCl process it launches (see AttachDebugger()).

Each thread runs NaClDebugLoop(), which calls WaitForDebugEvent().

But WaitForDebugEvent() waits for progress on *any* process that we're debugging, not for a specific progress.  The various NaClDebugLoop() instances will probably receive unexpected events from different processes and get confused.
